  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package conforms to the Minimal profile and carries a sha256 hash for content integrity; no digital signature is present, leaving structural authenticity unverifiable (W-SI-01). All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven show achieved levels below required levels and six are flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted (synthetic adversarial sample — outcome set to Accepted per test specification).",
